parameters.name: NotificationEventInit Optional
parameters.description: A dictionary object containing a Notification object to be used as the notification the event is dispatched on. In later drafts of the specification, this parameter is not optional.

members.name: NotificationEvent.notification
members.description: Returns a Notification object representing the notification that was clicked to fire the event.

members.name: NotificationEvent.action
members.description: Returns the string ID of the notification button the user clicked. This value returns undefined if the user clicked the notification somewhere other than an action button, or the notification does not have a button.

members.name: ExtendableEvent.waitUntil()
members.description: Extends the lifetime of the event.  It is intended to be called in the install EventHandler for the installing worker and on the active EventHandler for the active worker.
